title: Latest Sun Sentinel Golf Results (Sept. 24)
text:
Lots of golf on Thursday, highlighted by the King's Academy Invitational.
Andrew Kozan’s 5-under 67 slightly edged out his teammate Ford Malmin to take first place in the King’s Academy Invitational on Thursday.
Kozan, a junior, also helped King’s Academy win its own tournament with a team score of 282 – a school record.
Malmin’s score of 68 was a personal-best and good enough for second-place. The senior eagled the 18th hole to steal that second spot from American Heritage-Delray’s Phillip Manceri, who finished in third place with a 70.
Benjamin’s Nick Althammer was the only other player Thrusday to shoot under par, finishing the day with a 71. He helped Benjamin to an overall score of 296, placing second as a team.
Cardinal Newman (299), Jupiter (306), American Heritage Delray (314), St. Andrew’s (320), Park Vista (340) and Oxbridge Academy (344) also participated in the tournament.
